# AI Odyssey - MERN Stack Implementation Plan

The user requested to transition the website to the MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) stack and to create an animated Ultron greeting using `anime.js` directly.

## Architecture Change
The current static HTML/CSS/JS files will be removed or repurposed. We will split the project into two main directories:
- `/frontend`: A React application (built with Vite).
- `/backend`: A Node.js/Express application with MongoDB connection.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Initialization & Cleanup
- Delete `index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js`.
- Initialize `/backend` with `npm init -y`, `express`, `mongoose`, `cors`, `dotenv`.
- Initialize `/frontend` using `npx create-vite@latest frontend --template react`.

### 2. Backend Implementation
#### [NEW] `backend/server.js`
- Setup Express server.
- Connect to MongoDB via Mongoose.
- Create a simple Registration API endpoint (since the UI has a "Register Now" button).
#### [NEW] `backend/models/User.js`
- Mongoose schema for user registration (Name, Email, etc.).

### 3. Frontend Implementation
#### [MODIFY] `frontend/src/components/MainOverlay.jsx`
- Reorder and expand the layout to match the requested structure:
  1. Hero section with Timer
  2. **[NEW]** AI Department section
  3. About AI Odyssey section
  4. **[MODIFY]** Games section with the following games: Catch the word, Quiz, Treasure Hunt, Escape Room, AI or NOT, Mini Shark Tank, Binary Coding. Each game gets "Rule Book" and "About It" buttons.
  5. **[MODIFY]** Registration section (add criteria and registration button)
  6. **[NEW]** Previous AI Odyssey section
  7. **[NEW]** Sponsors section
- Update the Navbar links to include these new targets.

#### [MODIFY] `frontend/src/index.css`
- Add necessary styling for the sponsor grids, previous odyssey showcase, and the updated game cards layout to ensure they look stunning in 3 columns.

## Verification Plan
- Run the backend on port 5000 and frontend on port 5173.
- Verify the Anime.js SVG animation of Ultron.
- Ensure the React conversion matches the original aesthetic.
- (Optional) Test the registration endpoint.
